culiarly Russian attitude toward history and to allow us to read some major works of Russian literature in a new light. The book will be of interest not only to Slavists, but to anyone concerned with the interaction between history and literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 4aLiterary Studies -- General Criticism and Theory. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080476678440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804766784423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780804766784/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles